.TH "hxcfe" "1" "2026-06-09" "HxC Floppy Emulator User Manual" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
hxcfe - command-line floppy disk image converter and USB HxC floppy
server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]hxcfe\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]hxcfe\f[R] is the command-line companion to the HxC Floppy Emulator
hardware devices.
It exposes the full power of the \f[B]libhxcfe\f[R] library through a
simple command-line interface and allows users to convert floppy disk
images between many formats, apply raw disk layouts, list or extract
files from floppy images, and drive a USB HxC Floppy Emulator device as
a floppy image server.
.PP
Multiple \f[B]-conv\f[R] / \f[B]-foutput\f[R] pairs may be given in a
single invocation to produce several output formats at once.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-help\f[R]
Display a summary of available options and usage examples.
.TP
\f[B]-license\f[R]
Print the full license text.
.TP
\f[B]-verbose\f[R]
Enable verbose output.
.TP
\f[B]-script\f[R]:\f[I]filename\f[R]
Execute the batch script \f[I]filename\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-modulelist\f[R]
List all supported floppy image formats (FORMAT identifiers) with their
access mode (R = read, W = write) and file extensions.
.TP
\f[B]-rawlist\f[R]
List all available raw disk layouts (DISKLAYOUT identifiers).
.TP
\f[B]-interfacelist\f[R]
List all available floppy interface modes (INTERFACE_MODE identifiers).
.TP
\f[B]-finput\f[R]:\f[I]filename\f[R]
Specify the input floppy image file.
.TP
\f[B]-foutput\f[R]:\f[I]filename\f[R]
Specify the output floppy image file.
.TP
\f[B]-conv\f[R]:\f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
Convert the input image to the given format.
Use \f[B]-modulelist\f[R] for the list of valid FORMAT values.
.TP
\f[B]-reffile\f[R]:\f[I]filename\f[R]
Sector-to-sector copy mode.
Use \f[I]filename\f[R] as the reference image that provides the disk
layout; each sector is then updated from the input image.
Must be combined with \f[B]-conv\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-uselayout\f[R]:\f[I]DISKLAYOUT\f[R]
Apply the raw disk layout \f[I]DISKLAYOUT\f[R] to the image.
Use \f[B]-rawlist\f[R] for the list of valid DISKLAYOUT values.
.TP
\f[B]-usb\f[R]:\f[I]DRIVE\f[R]
Start the USB HxC Floppy Emulator server using \f[I]DRIVE\f[R] as the
floppy image.
.TP
\f[B]-infos\f[R]
Print detailed information about the input image.
.TP
\f[B]-ifmode\f[R]:\f[I]INTERFACE_MODE\f[R]
Select the floppy interface mode.
Use \f[B]-interfacelist\f[R] for valid values.
.TP
\f[B]-singlestep\f[R]
Force single-step mode when writing the output image.
.TP
\f[B]-doublestep\f[R]
Force double-step mode when writing the output image.
.TP
\f[B]-list\f[R]
List the files contained in the floppy image.
.TP
\f[B]-getfile\f[R]:\f[I]FILE\f[R]
Extract \f[I]FILE\f[R] from the floppy image to the current directory.
.TP
\f[B]-putfile\f[R]:\f[I]FILE\f[R]
Inject \f[I]FILE\f[R] into the floppy image.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Convert a disk image to HFE format:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
hxcfe -finput:\[dq]input.img\[dq] -conv:HXC_HFE -foutput:\[dq]output.hfe\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Convert a disk image to both HFE and BMP in one pass:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
hxcfe -finput:\[dq]input.img\[dq] -conv:HXC_HFE -foutput:\[dq]output.hfe\[dq] \[rs]
      -conv:BMP_DISK_IMAGE -foutput:\[dq]output.bmp\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Convert a raw image to HFE using a specific disk layout:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
hxcfe -finput:\[dq]input.img\[dq] -uselayout:PUMA_ROBOT_DD_640KB \[rs]
      -conv:HXC_HFE -foutput:\[dq]output.hfe\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Generate an empty HFE image from a disk layout (no input image needed):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
hxcfe -uselayout:PUMA_ROBOT_DD_640KB -conv:HXC_HFE -foutput:\[dq]output.hfe\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Sector-to-sector copy using a reference image for the layout:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
hxcfe -finput:\[dq]input.hfe\[dq] -conv:HXC_HFE -foutput:\[dq]output.hfe\[dq] \[rs]
      -reffile:\[dq]reference.hfe\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
